2.01	Cholac	Lactulose	Lactulose is a synthetic, non-digestible sugar used in the treatment of chronic constipation and hepatic encephalopathy, a complication of liver disease. It is a disaccharide (double-sugar) formed from one molecule each of the simple sugars (monosaccharides) fructose and galactose. It is produced commercially by isomerization of lactose.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Lactulose2.png/300px-Lactulose2.png
